(710, 2, '2020-12-20 15:12:25', '2020-12-20 15:12:25', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mangroves are woody plants that grow at the interface between land and sea in tropical and sub-tropical latitudes where they exist in conditions of high salinity, extreme tides, strong winds, high temperatures and muddy, anaerobic soils. There may be no other group of plants with such highly developed morphological and physiological adaptations to extreme conditions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mangrove forests occupy about 15 million hectares of tropical and subtropical coastline worldwide.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Mangrove in Keylakunu', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mangrove-in-keylakunu', '', '', '2020-12-20 15:12:39', '2020-12-20 15:12:39', '', 0, 'http://experiencemaldives.online/?page_id=710', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(711, 2, '2020-12-20 15:12:25', '2020-12-20 15:12:25', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mangroves are woody plants that grow at the interface between land and sea in tropical and sub-tropical latitudes where they exist in conditions of high salinity, extreme tides, strong winds, high temperatures and muddy, anaerobic soils. There may be no other group of plants with such highly developed morphological and physiological adaptations to extreme conditions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mangrove forests occupy about 15 million hectares of tropical and subtropical coastline worldwide.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Mangrove in Keylakunu', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '710-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-12-20 15:12:25', '2020-12-20 15:12:25', '', 710, 'http://experiencemaldives.online/2020/12/20/710-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(712, 2, '2020-12-20 15:14:01', '2020-12-20 15:14:01', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most prominent <strong>mangrove</strong> in the area is the small-leafed orange <strong>mangrove</strong>, locally called kan\'doo. Residents of <strong>Neykurendhoo</strong> grew up by sourcing food from these trees. The strong wood from the small-leafed orange <strong>mangroves</strong> was used to build boats. The area is nature\'s gift for the island and remains as its pride</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Mangrove in Neykurendhoo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mangrove-in-neykurendhoo', '', '', '2020-12-20 15:14:08', '2020-12-20 15:14:08', '', 0, 'http://experiencemaldives.online/?page_id=712', 0, 'page', '', 0),
